                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13673443" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 3 Jun 2013 19:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If multiple hosts are specified, then RemoteHTable will round robin requests. This won&apos;t work with scanners, because scanners are stateful. (Yes, technically not RESTful...) When scanning, connect only to a single REST gateway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13674135" author="bjhuangg" created="Tue, 4 Jun 2013 07:29:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, there are some solutions recommended? If we can not startup multiple servers, how I can make full use of loading balacne, such as Nginx?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13674163" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 4 Jun 2013 08:24:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Scanners are stateful. When you open a scanner, the REST gateway sends back a URL for the scan resource. You must use that URL/server only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every other op can be dispatched to multiple servers no problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
